@low  add tailwind merge to useTheme
@low  add possibility to use app.config to overwrite theme:
    - write file to .nuxt/theme/app.config.ts
    - module needs to add it with nuxt hook:
    const appConfigFile = await resolvePath(resolve(runtimeDir, 'app.config'))
    nuxt.hook('app:resolve', (app) => {
        app.configs.push(appConfigFile)
    })
    - app.config should use this style:
    {
        theme: {
            extend: {
                default: {...},
                admin: {...}
            }
        }
    }
@high add possibility to insert theme directly to useTheme and not via string (vite plugin needs to ignore it) -> this is a typescript thing
        - we need this for the case someone writes a nuxt module that uses the theme, if using extend with layers this is not needed
        import { useTheme, buttonTheme } from '#imports'
        useTheme(buttonTheme)
@high add options function for useTheme -> use dot notations to get options